cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the development of a deep end-to-end model for automatic food places recognition by analyzing egocentric photo-streams. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning models for classification also falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of image retrieval techniques, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of human behavior in relation to food events, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
